ce of Crowd Control, was it too much?</span><hr size=1> From a slightly different poitn of view, I think the fact that CC is simply not fun for the majority of the people involved must be taken into account.<br>
I think that each of the primary CC classes should also get CCC abilities - ie. Counterspells which greatly reduce the duration of mes on a target, group, or even AE target, or AE ground target.  There are many possibilities to be found by mixing target types with magnitude of effects, area of effect, and timers.  I think heals are too general of a counter - The anti-CC should be in the hands of the CCers themselves (After all, they are the ones who understand how it works best, naturally they would be the ones who knew how to remove it)<br>
What this does is provide a counter to CC without making the CC classes irrelevant.  With a good strategy, CC would still be a viable tactics (ie. Assassins take out all the enemy CCers just as your CCers run in to AE mes - No more CCC for the enemy) yet it would no longer be so unstoppable.  A BT equivalent for CC (With a timer after it is removed until it can be reapplied) would even be a possibility - so long as it was only given to the primary CC classes.<br>
If we take away the power of the primary ability of a class, we must give them something back.  I think that making the CCers the primary counter to other CCers is the right solution, with the overall benefit being to the other classes, for whom the primary effect will be to not be CCed as much.<br>
<br>
All this off the top of my head, so likely many holes in it, but seems a good idea to me.<br>
<br>
EDIT:  Ela, come to think of it, shouldn't there be a forum for the CC classes?   Unfortunately, I think some of the categories still group together classes that aren't as related as they may appear to be (Musicians for instance.)<br>
Might I suggest reorganizing based purely on roles, and not restricting a class to one role?  That way a crowd control forum might include Bards, Sorcerors, Mentalists, Skalds, Healers... The primary and the non primary CC, most of whom seem to fall into different categories at the moment. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A> at: 6/28/02 9:21:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Yin Yang Grandmaster</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#DEB887>(6/28/02 11:36:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The new face of Crowd Control, was it too much?</span><hr size=1> I'm going to leave the initial groupings in the class section, but I can add another forum for just CC classes and issues. It'll be up shortly when I scrounge some time between work and see how it goes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=3.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showNextMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fyinyangofcamelotfrm16.emailToFriend?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif borde